<P>
Forces the widet used by dynamic dialog to represent an attribute.<BR>
By default, dynamic dialog selects the best widget to use from the following rules.<BR>

</P>
<H2>
Fields
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>
CheckBox if the attribute is boolean
<LI>
DatePicker if the attribute is a date
<LI>
TextField if no choice
<LI>
RadioButton if <= 4 choices
<LI>
ComboBox if <= 20 choices
<LI>
LookupTextField if > 20 choices
</UL>
<P>

</P>
<H2>
Containers
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>
TaskPane or widget defined in 'defaultContainerWidget' &nbsp;if the parameter 'group' is evaluated to true
<LI>
otherwise it reuses the parent container
</UL>
<P>

</P>
<H2>
Lists
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>
Table allways
</UL>
